  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering is complex and involves multiple levels of legislation and regulations:\n\n1. International Level\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Components\n- Criminal penalties for money laundering\n- Asset seizure provisions\n- Mandatory reporting for financial institutions\n- Enhanced due diligence procedures\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement investigations\n- Civil and criminal prosecution\n- International cooperation between jurisdictions\n\n5. Regulatory Compliance\n- Risk assessment procedures\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Record-keeping requirements\n- Employee training programs\n\n6. Specific Prohibited Activities\n- Concealing financial origins\n- Disguising illegal proceeds\n- Transferring illicit funds\n- Layering financial transactions\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining transparency in global financial systems.",
